ZH: 细胞是构成生物体的基本单位。
EN: Cells are the basic units that make up living organisms.

ZH: 细胞在人体内不断分裂和再生。
EN: Cells continuously divide and regenerate in the human body.

ZH: 人体细胞的数量超过了数十万亿。
EN: The number of cells in the human body exceeds trillions.

ZH: 细胞壁起到保护和支撑细胞的作用。
EN: The cell wall serves to protect and support the cell.

ZH: 细胞负责执行生物体的所有功能。
EN: Cells are responsible for carrying out all the functions of living organisms.

ZH: 细胞核包含着遗传物质DNA。
EN: The cell nucleus contains the genetic material DNA.

ZH: 细胞膜是控制物质进出细胞的关键。
EN: The cell membrane is key to controlling the movement of substances in and out of the cell.

ZH: 细胞间质填充在细胞器与细胞膜之间。
EN: The cytoplasm fills the space between organelles and the cell membrane.

ZH: 细胞器如线粒体和高尔基体发挥特定功能。
EN: Organelles such as mitochondria and Golgi apparatus perform specific functions in the cell.

ZH: 一些细胞具有特殊功能，如神经细胞传递电信号。
EN: Some cells have specialized functions, such as nerve cells transmitting electrical signals.

ZH: 细胞分化使得细胞能够担任不同的角色。
EN: Cell differentiation allows cells to take on different roles.

ZH: 在细胞分裂过程中，细胞会复制自身的遗传信息。
EN: During cell division, cells replicate their genetic information.

ZH: 干细胞具有多能性，能够分化成多种细胞类型。
EN: Stem cells have pluripotency and can differentiate into various cell types.

ZH: 某些疾病可以通过调整细胞的功能来治疗。
EN: Some diseases can be treated by modifying the function of cells.

ZH: 基因工程可以改变细胞的基因组成。
EN: Genetic engineering can alter the genetic composition of cells.

ZH: 细胞的正常功能受到环境因素的影响。
EN: The normal function of cells is influenced by environmental factors.

ZH: 细胞自噬是一种调节细胞内营养和代谢平衡的过程。
EN: Cell autophagy is a process that regulates the nutrient and metabolic balance within cells.

ZH: 细胞凋亡是组织发育和维持稳态的重要机制。
EN: Cell apoptosis is an important mechanism for tissue development and maintaining homeostasis.

ZH: 细胞膜的渗透性决定了物质进出细胞的速度。
EN: The permeability of the cell membrane determines the rate at which substances enter and leave the cell.

ZH: 细胞内的代谢过程需要催化剂来加快化学反应速度。
EN: Metabolic processes within cells require catalysts to accelerate chemical reactions.
